WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:27.200
CHAPTER I A LETTER FOR ADAM

00:27.200 --> 00:34.000
One day a postman came to my village. The postman brought me a letter from my son,

00:34.000 --> 00:35.000
Sol.

00:35.000 --> 00:38.840
"'Is your name, Adam?' the postman asked.

00:38.840 --> 00:40.560
"'Yes,' I said.

00:40.560 --> 00:45.680
"'I've got a letter for you,' the postman read the envelope.

00:45.680 --> 00:51.120
"'Adam of the village of Minta, a letter from me?

00:51.120 --> 00:54.880
"'Who is it from?' I asked.

00:54.920 --> 00:58.360
"'The postman looked at the envelope again.

00:58.360 --> 01:01.520
"'From Sol,' he said.

01:01.520 --> 01:07.800
"'He gave me the letter and walked away.

01:07.800 --> 01:12.240
"'Martha, Martha!' I called to my wife.

01:12.240 --> 01:13.400
"'Come here.

01:13.400 --> 01:17.960
"'We have a letter from our son Sol.'

01:17.960 --> 01:21.120
"'Martha came out and looked at the letter.

01:21.120 --> 01:25.200
"'I was excited, but she was also worried.

01:25.200 --> 01:28.080
"'A letter from Sol,' she said.

01:28.080 --> 01:30.640
"'Is he alive and well?

01:30.640 --> 01:33.200
"'I'm going to find the schoolteacher.'

01:33.200 --> 01:36.320
"'He can read the letter.'

01:36.320 --> 01:39.400
"'There was no school fifty years ago,

01:39.400 --> 01:42.720
"'so I cannot read or write.

01:42.720 --> 01:44.960
"'I live in a small village.

01:44.960 --> 01:47.560
"'The only work is farming.

01:47.560 --> 01:51.920
"'My only son Sol left the village two years ago,

01:51.920 --> 01:54.760
"'and my three daughters are married.

01:54.760 --> 02:00.040
"'Sol is making a lot of money in a foreign country.

02:00.040 --> 02:03.520
"'Martha and the schoolteacher came back.

02:03.520 --> 02:05.720
"'A lot of other people came.

02:05.720 --> 02:09.520
"'Everyone wanted to hear my letter.

02:09.520 --> 02:14.920
"'The schoolteacher opened the envelope and read the letter.

02:18.440 --> 02:25.800
"'20 Taylor Street, London E-19, England 16th of March.

02:25.800 --> 02:29.920
"'Dear father, I am living in London.

02:29.920 --> 02:32.920
"'I have a job in a factory.

02:32.920 --> 02:35.320
"'The work is very hard.

02:35.320 --> 02:39.920
"'I often work at night, but the pay is good.

02:39.920 --> 02:44.640
"'I am well, and I live with people from my country.

02:44.640 --> 02:47.520
"'I am well, and I live with people from my country.

02:47.520 --> 02:52.440
"'I am sending you one hundred pounds in this letter.

02:52.440 --> 02:56.000
"'This is for you and my mother.

02:56.000 --> 03:02.360
"'Love to you and mother, Sol.

03:02.360 --> 03:06.720
"'One hundred pounds, I said to the schoolteacher,

03:06.720 --> 03:08.000
"'You're wrong.

03:08.000 --> 03:09.840
"'It's a mistake.

03:09.840 --> 03:12.360
"'No,' the schoolteacher said,

03:12.360 --> 03:13.760
"'I'm not wrong.

03:13.760 --> 03:15.480
"'It's not a mistake.

03:15.480 --> 03:17.480
"'Here is the money.

03:17.480 --> 03:20.560
"'And he gave me a piece of paper.

03:20.560 --> 03:23.120
"'What is this?' I asked.

03:23.120 --> 03:26.480
"'A money order,' the schoolteacher said.

03:26.480 --> 03:28.600
"'Go to Darpur.

03:28.600 --> 03:33.320
"'Take this money order to the post office in Darpur.

03:33.320 --> 03:37.240
"'The money order is worth one hundred pounds.

03:37.240 --> 03:41.440
"'The post office official will give you the money.

03:41.440 --> 03:45.960
"'One hundred pounds,' I said again.

03:45.960 --> 03:48.000
"'Everyone laughed and said,

03:48.000 --> 03:50.680
"'Adam, you are a rich man.

03:50.680 --> 03:54.960
"'You can buy many things for your farm and for your house.

03:54.960 --> 03:59.640
"'And I can buy some good food and drink in Darpur.

03:59.640 --> 04:03.000
"'I am going to give a party for you all.'

04:03.000 --> 04:07.000
"'I told my friends, Martha said,

04:07.000 --> 04:09.400
"'Sole is a good son.'"

04:09.400 --> 04:20.520
That evening, the village people talked about the money order and my money.

04:20.520 --> 04:23.920
Martha and I also talked about the money.

04:23.920 --> 04:26.760
We needed many things for the farm.

04:40.400 --> 04:44.680
Chapter Two, Adam Goes to Darpur.

04:48.120 --> 04:51.280
The next morning, I got up very early.

04:51.280 --> 04:54.400
It was dark and everyone was asleep,

04:54.400 --> 04:57.400
but I was going to Darpur.

04:57.400 --> 05:00.240
I washed and dressed carefully.

05:00.240 --> 05:04.680
I put on my best clothes and I carried my best stick.

05:04.680 --> 05:07.960
I put the money order carefully in my pocket

05:08.200 --> 05:12.120
and I said, goodbye to Martha.

05:12.120 --> 05:15.400
I walked ten miles to the main road.

05:15.400 --> 05:21.800
I sat down at the main road and ate my breakfast.

05:21.800 --> 05:24.440
I waited for the bus.

05:24.440 --> 05:27.640
I waited for two hours.

05:27.640 --> 05:31.080
Then the bus came and I got on.

05:37.960 --> 05:40.440
It is a long way to Darpur.

05:40.440 --> 05:43.960
The bus takes three hours.

05:43.960 --> 05:48.800
I arrived in Darpur and walked to the post office immediately.

05:48.800 --> 05:51.080
I do not often go to Darpur.

05:51.080 --> 05:54.480
I only know the market and one shop.

05:54.480 --> 05:56.640
This is the shop of Rick.

05:56.640 --> 06:00.440
I buy things for my farm from Rick.

06:00.440 --> 06:03.560
There were a lot of people in the post office.

06:03.560 --> 06:06.480
I asked about money orders.

06:06.480 --> 06:09.080
A man showed me the queue.

06:09.080 --> 06:15.960
There was a long line of people and I waited at the back.

06:15.960 --> 06:18.200
Finally it was my turn.

06:18.200 --> 06:20.800
I was at the front of the queue.

06:20.800 --> 06:24.120
But the official did not serve me.

06:24.120 --> 06:27.160
Excuse me, I said, it's my turn.

06:27.160 --> 06:28.920
I'm next.

06:28.920 --> 06:30.440
You are next.

06:30.440 --> 06:33.080
Oh man, I'm very busy.

06:33.080 --> 06:35.520
The official said, look at my papers.

06:35.520 --> 06:37.320
Look at all these people.

06:37.320 --> 06:42.440
I am very busy and you must wait.

06:42.440 --> 06:44.560
So I waited.

06:44.560 --> 06:47.760
Finally, the official looked at me.

06:47.760 --> 06:49.040
What do you want?

06:49.040 --> 06:50.480
He asked.

06:50.480 --> 06:52.600
I gave him my money order.

06:52.600 --> 06:57.600
This is my money order for 100 pounds, I replied.

06:57.600 --> 07:00.200
The official held out his hand.

07:00.200 --> 07:04.200
Identity card, he said.

07:04.200 --> 07:08.840
Excuse me, I don't understand, I replied.

07:08.840 --> 07:12.000
Your identity card, the official said again,

07:12.000 --> 07:15.560
give me your identity card.

07:15.560 --> 07:17.920
What is an identity card?

07:17.920 --> 07:19.400
I asked.

07:19.400 --> 07:23.040
I can't give you any money for this money order.

07:23.040 --> 07:26.160
First, I must see your identity card.

07:26.160 --> 07:29.800
Your identity card gives your name and your address.

07:29.800 --> 07:32.680
Your identity card describes you.

07:32.680 --> 07:35.640
There is a photograph of you in your identity card.

07:35.640 --> 07:37.440
I don't know you.

07:37.440 --> 07:39.440
Who are you?

07:39.440 --> 07:44.160
The official was a little angry, but I was also angry.

07:44.160 --> 07:45.280
Who am I?

07:45.280 --> 07:47.960
I said, everyone knows me.

07:47.960 --> 07:50.760
I am Adam of the village of Minter.

07:50.760 --> 07:55.800
I haven't got an identity card and I don't need an identity card.

07:55.800 --> 08:00.240
Oh man, I'm very busy and you're very stupid.

08:00.240 --> 08:04.640
The official said, who are you, where is Minter?

08:04.640 --> 08:11.040
Give me my money, give me my 100 pounds, I said.

08:11.040 --> 08:19.160
The official looked angry and said, show me your identity card, I don't know you.

08:19.160 --> 08:25.240
The official gave back my money order and he turned away.

08:25.240 --> 08:27.840
Where can I buy an identity card?

08:27.840 --> 08:29.920
I asked the official.

08:29.920 --> 08:31.680
He did not speak to me.

08:31.680 --> 08:34.000
He did not answer.

08:34.000 --> 08:37.680
Go to the ministry of the interior, a man said.

08:37.680 --> 08:57.160
He was standing in the queue and he told me the way.

08:57.160 --> 09:02.400
To three, an identity card.

09:02.400 --> 09:05.720
I walked to the ministry of the interior.

09:05.720 --> 09:08.280
I waited in another queue.

09:08.280 --> 09:11.160
I spoke to another official.

09:11.160 --> 09:14.680
I asked for an identity card.

09:14.680 --> 09:20.080
Filling this application form, the official said, and bring the form and three photographs

09:20.080 --> 09:24.240
of yourself and two pounds, come back tomorrow.

09:24.240 --> 09:26.600
Tomorrow, I said.

09:26.600 --> 09:29.200
Can I have an identity card today, please?

09:29.200 --> 09:30.200
I live in Minter.

09:30.200 --> 09:33.080
I live five hours journey from Darpur.

09:33.080 --> 09:34.800
I'm an old man.

09:34.800 --> 09:37.360
Yes, come back tomorrow.

09:37.360 --> 09:41.800
And the official turned away.

09:41.800 --> 09:45.400
I walked away from the ministry of the interior.

09:45.400 --> 09:47.760
I walked to the market.

09:47.760 --> 09:50.280
At the market, I looked at everyone.

09:50.280 --> 09:55.560
I was looking for a man from my village, but I could not find a villager.

09:55.560 --> 09:58.480
So then I walked to the shop of Rick.

09:58.480 --> 10:00.400
I spoke to Rick.

10:00.400 --> 10:06.920
I want an identity card, I told him, but I need three photographs of myself.

10:06.920 --> 10:11.000
I see you need some photographs.

10:11.000 --> 10:17.920
And he showed me the way to a photographer.

10:17.920 --> 10:19.760
I found the house.

10:19.760 --> 10:23.720
The photographer was asleep, but he came to me quickly.

10:23.720 --> 10:27.840
The man's clothes were dirty, and he looked tired.

10:27.840 --> 10:30.600
I need an identity card, I said.

10:30.600 --> 10:33.560
I want three photographs of myself.

10:33.560 --> 10:40.120
Yes, you want three photographs of yourself, the photographer replied, and I take very

10:40.120 --> 10:41.920
good photographs.

10:41.920 --> 10:44.360
Come and see my camera.

10:44.360 --> 10:46.520
We walked into his room.

10:46.520 --> 10:49.520
In the middle of the room was a large camera.

10:49.520 --> 10:52.440
This is the best camera in Darpur.

10:52.440 --> 10:55.800
This camera is very, very good.

10:55.800 --> 10:58.000
The photographer said proudly.

10:58.000 --> 11:01.560
I've never seen a camera, I said.

11:01.560 --> 11:03.560
I don't know about cameras.

11:03.560 --> 11:07.800
Hurry up and take a photograph of me.

11:07.800 --> 11:10.960
Please do not hurry me, old man.

11:10.960 --> 11:18.040
The photographer said I am an artist, and he gave me a mirror and a comb.

11:18.040 --> 11:21.200
I don't want a mirror, I don't want a comb.

11:21.200 --> 11:23.400
Please take my photograph.

11:23.400 --> 11:27.040
I'm going to mint over this afternoon, and I'm in a hurry.

11:27.040 --> 11:30.000
I said, yes, he said.

11:30.000 --> 11:32.200
But first, the price.

11:32.200 --> 11:37.640
This is the best camera in Darpur, and I'm the best photographer.

11:37.640 --> 11:45.720
Three photographs will cost you two pounds fifty, two pounds fifty, and I laughed.

11:46.200 --> 11:49.360
Two pounds fifty, and pay me now, please.

11:49.360 --> 11:52.200
The photographer answered.

11:52.200 --> 11:55.320
I did not know the price of photographs.

11:55.320 --> 11:57.240
What could I do?

11:57.240 --> 12:01.680
Then the photographer said, you're an old man.

12:01.680 --> 12:06.520
For you, the price is two pounds.

12:06.520 --> 12:11.040
So I gave him the money, and he took the photographs.

12:11.040 --> 12:13.160
Come back tomorrow morning, he said.

12:13.160 --> 12:16.160
I want my three photographs now, immediately.

12:16.160 --> 12:18.640
I said, don't be stupid.

12:18.640 --> 12:22.720
The photographer said, photographs take twenty-four hours.

12:22.720 --> 12:25.520
Come back tomorrow.

12:25.520 --> 12:27.120
What could I do?

12:27.120 --> 12:33.200
So I said, yes, tomorrow morning, good, said the photographer.

12:33.200 --> 12:37.880
Now go, I have a lot of work, I'm very busy.

12:37.880 --> 12:40.560
I went back to the bus station.

12:40.560 --> 12:43.480
I sat on the bus for three hours.

12:43.480 --> 12:47.680
I walked ten miles back to my village.

12:47.680 --> 12:51.000
It was night time, and I was very tired.

12:51.000 --> 12:54.920
Martha and my friends were waiting for me.

12:54.920 --> 12:56.600
Where is the money?

12:56.600 --> 13:00.600
Martha asked.

13:00.600 --> 13:02.280
I have no money.

13:02.280 --> 13:05.000
I cannot change the money order.

13:05.000 --> 13:08.280
First I must have an identity card.

13:08.280 --> 13:12.720
And I told Martha everything.

13:12.720 --> 13:14.960
Tomorrow I'm going to dark poor again.

13:14.960 --> 13:19.360
I said, then I did not talk again.

13:19.360 --> 13:23.560
I was very tired, and it was late at night.

13:23.560 --> 13:37.560
I lay on my bed, and I slept.

13:37.560 --> 13:42.920
After four, no photographs.

13:42.920 --> 13:45.400
I woke up late the next morning.

13:45.400 --> 13:47.920
The sun was already high.

13:47.920 --> 13:51.200
I did not walk to the main road and catch a bus.

13:51.200 --> 13:55.240
All the buses go to dark poor early in the morning.

13:55.240 --> 13:57.360
So I stayed at home on Wednesday.

13:57.360 --> 13:59.760
I was still very tired.

13:59.760 --> 14:03.520
I rested and talked to the villagers about the money order.

14:03.520 --> 14:07.280
I told them about the identity card and the photographer.

14:07.280 --> 14:11.360
The schoolteacher said, yes, the official is correct.

14:11.360 --> 14:16.360
In a post office you always show your identity card.

14:16.360 --> 14:23.640
The schoolteacher filled in my application form for an identity card.

14:23.640 --> 14:27.720
Application form for identity card.

14:27.720 --> 14:31.280
Name Adam Jami.

14:31.280 --> 14:38.600
This village of minter, age 72 years.

14:38.600 --> 14:51.600
Place of birth, village of minter, occupation, farmer, color of eyes, brown.

14:51.600 --> 14:55.120
On Thursday I traveled to dark poor again.

14:55.120 --> 14:59.320
I walked to the main road and I caught a bus.

14:59.320 --> 15:03.920
In dark poor I walked to the house of the photographer.

15:03.920 --> 15:07.160
I knocked on the door of the house.

15:07.160 --> 15:09.080
No one came to the door.

15:09.080 --> 15:11.560
I knocked again loudly with my stick.

15:11.560 --> 15:13.720
A woman opened the door.

15:13.720 --> 15:15.280
Who are you?

15:15.280 --> 15:16.360
What do you want?

15:16.360 --> 15:17.440
She asked.

15:17.440 --> 15:19.640
Can I have my photographs please?

15:19.640 --> 15:21.280
I said, your photographs?

15:21.280 --> 15:22.880
I have no photographs.

15:22.880 --> 15:24.600
The woman replied.

15:24.600 --> 15:26.560
I came here on Tuesday.

15:26.560 --> 15:28.120
Where is the photographer?

15:28.120 --> 15:29.120
I asked.

15:29.120 --> 15:30.120
He's out.

15:30.120 --> 15:31.840
He's not here.

15:31.840 --> 15:36.080
And the woman closed the door.

15:36.080 --> 15:37.800
I shouted at her.

15:37.800 --> 15:41.520
I'm waiting here for him.

15:41.520 --> 15:44.680
After a long time the photographer came back.

15:44.680 --> 15:48.640
He looked tired and he smelt a beer.

15:48.640 --> 15:49.840
Give me my photographs.

15:49.840 --> 15:53.520
I said, I have waited a long time for you.

15:53.520 --> 15:58.080
The photographer looked at me and said, I don't know you old man.

15:59.080 --> 16:01.640
What photographs are you talking about?

16:01.640 --> 16:04.880
My three photographs from my identity card.

16:04.880 --> 16:08.000
I paid you two pounds for them on Tuesday.

16:08.000 --> 16:11.600
Give me my photographs immediately or my money.

16:11.600 --> 16:14.080
Your photographs, your money.

16:14.080 --> 16:15.840
What are you talking about?

16:15.840 --> 16:18.080
The photographer said, show me the paper.

16:18.080 --> 16:23.520
Show me the receipt for your money.

16:23.520 --> 16:25.080
My receipt?

16:25.080 --> 16:26.080
I asked.

16:26.080 --> 16:28.400
Yes, where is your receipt?

16:28.400 --> 16:30.400
The photographer asked.

16:30.400 --> 16:33.760
You didn't give me your receipt, I shouted.

16:33.760 --> 16:37.720
Give me my photographs, all my money immediately.

16:37.720 --> 16:40.960
And I hit the photographer hard with my stick.

16:40.960 --> 16:44.200
I am old, but I am still strong.

16:44.200 --> 16:46.480
The photographer fell on the ground.

16:46.480 --> 16:48.680
He shouted, help, help.

16:48.680 --> 16:51.200
This old man is killing me.

16:51.200 --> 16:54.080
And I hit him hard again.

16:54.080 --> 16:56.640
Lots of people ran out of their houses.

16:56.640 --> 17:00.400
I hit the photographer again, and two men held me.

17:00.400 --> 17:03.080
I could not get away from the two men.

17:03.080 --> 17:06.600
The photographer was very angry, and I was very angry.

17:06.600 --> 17:09.200
Lots of people were shouting.

17:09.200 --> 17:11.280
Then a policeman came.

17:11.280 --> 17:13.760
The photographer shouted to the policeman,

17:13.760 --> 17:16.680
this old man hit me three times with his stick.

17:16.680 --> 17:18.440
He's a thief and a murderer.

17:18.440 --> 17:20.520
He wants my money.

17:20.520 --> 17:23.280
The policeman held my arm and said,

17:23.280 --> 17:26.760
come with me to the police station.

17:26.760 --> 17:28.920
I did not say anything.

17:28.920 --> 17:30.600
We walked to the police station.

17:33.760 --> 17:37.120
At the police station, the policeman asked me,

17:37.120 --> 17:40.400
did you hit that man three times?

17:40.400 --> 17:42.120
Yes, I said.

17:42.120 --> 17:44.800
He didn't give me my photographs.

17:44.800 --> 17:48.800
Show me your identity card, said the policeman.

17:48.800 --> 17:51.200
I am Adam of Minter Village.

17:51.200 --> 17:54.080
I replied, and I haven't got an identity card.

17:56.960 --> 18:02.120
Old man, said the policeman, go back to your village.

18:02.120 --> 18:04.160
Don't come here and fight.

18:04.160 --> 18:06.920
Keep out of Darpur.

18:06.920 --> 18:08.440
And he pushed me into the street.

18:13.000 --> 18:15.440
I went back to my village.

18:15.440 --> 18:17.400
I was tired and angry.

18:22.200 --> 18:26.200
Chapter 5, Adam changes his money order.

18:28.200 --> 18:31.200
Next day, I told my story to all the villagers.

18:32.200 --> 18:34.200
The villagers were angry.

18:35.200 --> 18:37.200
Martha was very unhappy.

18:37.200 --> 18:40.200
She said, Saul is working very hard.

18:40.200 --> 18:43.200
He is sending money and we can't have the money.

18:43.200 --> 18:45.200
What are we going to do?

18:45.200 --> 18:47.200
I did not know.

18:47.200 --> 18:49.200
Then in the evening, the school teacher

18:49.200 --> 18:51.200
came to my house again.

18:51.200 --> 18:54.200
Adam, perhaps I can help you.

18:54.200 --> 18:58.200
The school teacher said, here is a letter to Mr. Sheth.

18:58.200 --> 19:00.200
Mr. Sheth?

19:00.200 --> 19:02.200
I said, who is he?

19:02.200 --> 19:07.200
He is an important man in Darpur, and he is a friend of my wife's cousin,

19:07.200 --> 19:09.200
replied the school teacher.

19:09.200 --> 19:11.200
This letter is to Mr. Sheth.

19:11.200 --> 19:14.200
The letter is about your money order.

19:14.200 --> 19:16.200
Perhaps he can help you.

19:17.200 --> 19:20.200
I took the letter and thanked the school teacher.

19:23.200 --> 19:28.200
So I traveled to Darpur again on Saturday for the third time.

19:29.200 --> 19:32.200
After a long time, I found Mr. Sheth's house.

19:33.200 --> 19:35.200
The door was opened by a tall man.

19:36.200 --> 19:38.200
Can I see Mr. Sheth?

19:38.200 --> 19:40.200
I asked, and who are you?

19:40.200 --> 19:45.200
The tall man asked, I have a letter for Mr. Sheth, I replied.

19:46.200 --> 19:47.200
I see.

19:47.200 --> 19:49.200
Can I have the letter, please?

19:49.200 --> 19:51.200
And the tall man held out his hand.

19:52.200 --> 19:54.200
The letter is here, I said.

19:54.200 --> 19:59.200
And I took the letter out of my pocket, but I must see Mr. Sheth.

19:59.200 --> 20:02.200
Many people want to see Mr. Sheth.

20:02.200 --> 20:07.200
The tall man told me, he is a very busy man and a very important man.

20:07.200 --> 20:13.200
Mr. Sheth is not here at the moment, but give me your letter and Mr. Sheth will read it later.

20:14.200 --> 20:16.200
I gave the tall man the letter.

20:17.200 --> 20:18.200
Then I waited.

20:19.200 --> 20:24.200
Later, a large black car came, and the man went into the house.

20:26.200 --> 20:30.200
A long time later, the tall man opened the door again.

20:31.200 --> 20:34.200
Come in now, please, and follow me, he said.

20:36.200 --> 20:37.200
I followed the tall man.

20:38.200 --> 20:42.200
We went into a large room with fine carpets and big chairs.

20:43.200 --> 20:45.200
Another man was in the room.

20:46.200 --> 20:47.200
He was drinking.

20:48.200 --> 20:51.200
This is Mr. Sheth, he said the tall man.

20:52.200 --> 20:56.200
I am Adam of Minter Village, I replied.

20:58.200 --> 21:01.200
Yes, I know, said Mr. Sheth.

21:02.200 --> 21:04.200
Thank you for the letter.

21:04.200 --> 21:08.200
I hope I can help you. I like to help people.

21:09.200 --> 21:11.200
Please, sit down.

21:12.200 --> 21:17.200
Mr. Sheth smiled. His clothes were new and smart.

21:18.200 --> 21:20.200
Thank you, I said.

21:21.200 --> 21:23.200
Can I see the money order, please?

21:24.200 --> 21:25.200
Mr. Sheth asked.

21:26.200 --> 21:28.200
I took the money order out of my pocket.

21:29.200 --> 21:33.200
By now, the money order was dirty and looked very old.

21:34.200 --> 21:36.200
I gave it to Mr. Sheth.

21:37.200 --> 21:40.200
This money order is for 100 pounds, I said.

21:41.200 --> 21:44.200
My son sent it from a foreign country.

21:45.200 --> 21:48.200
Mr. Sheth unfolded the money order and looked at it.

21:50.200 --> 21:53.200
You can't change this money order, he said.

21:53.200 --> 21:56.200
This money order is not worth 100 pounds.

21:57.200 --> 21:59.200
But this money order is worth nothing.

22:01.200 --> 22:02.200
Worth nothing.

22:03.200 --> 22:05.200
Worthless, I asked.

22:06.200 --> 22:09.200
Then Mr. Sheth looked at the money order again.

22:10.200 --> 22:12.200
Yes, worthless.

22:13.200 --> 22:16.200
Your son does not understand about money orders.

22:17.200 --> 22:20.200
This money order is not correct for our country.

22:20.200 --> 22:21.200
Mr. Sheth said.

22:22.200 --> 22:25.200
Then he looked at the money order again and said,

22:26.200 --> 22:28.200
And this money order is also old.

22:29.200 --> 22:30.200
It is out of date.

22:32.200 --> 22:33.200
I said nothing.

22:34.200 --> 22:37.200
Mr. Sheth gave me the money order back.

22:39.200 --> 22:41.200
Then Mr. Sheth smiled and said,

22:42.200 --> 22:44.200
I am very sorry.

22:45.200 --> 22:46.200
You are an old man.

22:46.200 --> 22:49.200
You came a long way from your village.

22:49.200 --> 22:52.200
What can I give you to eat and drink?

22:54.200 --> 22:56.200
I was not hungry.

22:57.200 --> 22:59.200
But Mr. Sheth went out of the room.

23:00.200 --> 23:03.200
Then he brought me some coffee and some cakes.

23:04.200 --> 23:05.200
I drank my coffee.

23:06.200 --> 23:10.200
Old man said, Mr. Sheth, I like to help people.

23:11.200 --> 23:13.200
I am a rich man.

23:13.200 --> 23:15.200
Give me your money order.

23:16.200 --> 23:19.200
I gave my money order to Mr. Sheth.

23:20.200 --> 23:24.200
Yes, this money order is worthless, he said again.

23:25.200 --> 23:27.200
But I am going to help you.

23:28.200 --> 23:31.200
I am going to change this money order for you.

23:32.200 --> 23:35.200
I am going to give you some money.

23:36.200 --> 23:38.200
Mr. Sheth went out of the room.

23:39.200 --> 23:41.200
I felt very happy again.

23:42.200 --> 23:45.200
After a few minutes, the tall man came into the room.

23:46.200 --> 23:48.200
He gave me an envelope.

23:49.200 --> 23:50.200
This is from Mr. Sheth.

23:51.200 --> 23:53.200
You can go now, the tall man said.

23:57.200 --> 23:59.200
I went out of the house.

24:00.200 --> 24:02.200
I walked along the road to the bus station.

24:03.200 --> 24:06.200
I opened the envelope and I took out my money.

24:07.200 --> 24:09.200
I counted the money.

24:10.200 --> 24:12.200
It was ten pounds.

24:14.200 --> 24:17.200
I thought about my only son, Saul.

24:19.200 --> 24:24.200
My son, Saul, had sent me a money order for one hundred pounds.

24:25.200 --> 24:28.200
Mr. Sheth had given me ten pounds.

24:29.200 --> 24:33.200
I felt old and I felt poor again.

24:39.200 --> 24:42.200
Mr. Sheth had given me ten pounds.

24:57.200 --> 25:00.200
Rich Man Poor Man was read by Sean Barrett

25:01.200 --> 25:06.200
and the recording produced by James Richardson at Studio AVP London.

